  <h2>📅 07/05/25</h2>

  <div class="news-item">
    <h2>🔥 Vulnerabilities</h2>

    <p>🧠 <b>Langflow RCE (CVE-2025-3248) Exploited in the Wild</b><br>
    Unsafe code validation in exposed Langflow instances enables RCE. Patch to 1.4.0 or isolate the service.<br>
    🔗 <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/critical-langflow-rce-flaw-exploited-to-hack-ai-app-servers/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

    <p>🖥️ <b>Samsung MagicINFO RCE (CVE-2024-7399) Actively Exploited</b><br>
    Path traversal in signage software enables malware delivery including Mirai variants. Update to 21.1050 or newer.<br>
    🔗 <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/samsung-magicinfo-9-server-rce-flaw-now-exploited-in-attacks/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

    <p>📦 <b>Apache Parquet Deserialization Flaw (CVE-2025-30065)</b><br>
    Public PoC allows instantiating Java classes from Avro in Parquet. Upgrade to 1.15.1 immediately.<br>
    🔗 <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/apache-parquet-exploit-tool-detect-servers-vulnerable-to-critical-flaw/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>
  </div>

