    <h2>🕵️ Adversaries & Attacks</h2>

    <p>🧪 <b>Infostealer Malware Surges 500% in 2024</b><br>
    Over 1.7B credentials leaked. Gen Z remains highly vulnerable due to password reuse.<br>
    🔗 <a href="https://www.cysecurity.news/2025/05/infostealer-malware-soars-500-as-17.html" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

    <p>🐼 <b>Smishing Triad’s Panda Shop Reaches 60M Victims Monthly</b><br>
    Uses Telegram, RCS, and OTP capture for wide-scale phishing-as-a-service. Cross-border action remains limited.<br>
    🔗 <a href="https://www.infosecurity-magazine.com/news/smishing-triad-upgrades-tools/" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

    <p>💥 <b>DieNet Hacktivists Launch Over 60 DDoS Attacks Since March</b><br>
    U.S. and Iraqi systems targeted via DDoS-as-a-service. No unique infrastructure identified.<br>
    🔗 <a href="https://www.netscout.com/blog/asert/profiling-dienet-new-hacktivist-threat" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

    <p>🕷️ <b>2.py Infostealer Combines Keylogger and Fake Login Server</b><br>
    Python RAT includes phishing server for Google/Microsoft. Low AV detection and active exfiltration to Telegram.<br>
    🔗 <a href="https://isc.sans.edu/diary/rss/31924" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

    <p>📂 <b>SAP NetWeaver CVE-2025-31324 Sees Second Wave of Attacks</b><br>
    New wave uses previously deployed webshells and open-source RCEs. Federal patching deadline: May 20.<br>
    🔗 <a href="https://securityaffairs.com/177522/hacking/experts-warn-of-a-second-wave-of-attacks-targeting-sap-netweaver-bug-cve-2025-31324.html" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

    <p>💳 <b>Panda Shop Smishing Kit Hits Apple Pay and Google Wallet</b><br>
    Updated kit sends 2M SMS/day. Advanced templates target card and mobile payment data globally.<br>
    🔗 <a href="https://securityaffairs.com/177502/cyber-crime/smishing-on-a-massive-scale-panda-shop-chinese-carding-syndicate.html" target="_blank">Read more</a></p>

    <p>🐇 <b>Reckless Rabbit Scams Use Facebook Ads, Deepfake Celebrities</b><br>
    Tied to Myanmar scam compounds and \$40B fraud economy. Cloaking, fake crypto sites, call centers used.<br>
